!! Our Sending God

Realized that as we get more churches in one area, we get more folks to focus on looking inwards and working with other churches. But this is slowly changing once more. If it is living, we say it is meant to reproduce. It is out of that concern that we ask what happened? What stopped it?

Three men influence all missionaries (before short term trips were popular). Don't talk about missions. "Go somewhere and do something."

!!! Learning from Otis Brady

Revolutionary from Argentina. Went to British Honduras. Though missionary would help them but he was taken into custody.
Stood in a circle and prayed. Otis Brady came to help (early on). Otis was just teaching the Word and assign them to tell the story through the city. All of these are new believers, young kids, isn't that a bad idea? Have some sort of strategy. Don't teach them the Word but teach them how to study the Word.

!!! Learning from George Patterson
Never teach something that they are not obeying. The obedience is what transforms their life and authenticates that God is who He says He is.

Immediate obedience vs wisdom. Without much counsel we cannot do well (verse on war etc.)
Proverbs 19:2 is a thing of wisdom. But knowledge can easily puff up. How then do we reconcile this fact?

!!! Learning form Charles Grock
"Wait in the element of miraculous in every work I start." For instance, go at a church where it needs to be started. Saw a woman at the window asking him if he was a Bible man. Said yes, and started teaching her. Never do anything that a new believer can't do. On Church Planting.


