Questions:

* What do you think His main point is in this passage?
* What are the probabilities and problems that we should expect?
* Where are we to sow?
** We are to sow everywhere.
* When do we stop sowing?

He doesn't give us a particular instruction where to sow. He does promise that there will be different kinds of responses. All the seeds are sown but we will see all kinds of responses. It is guaranteed that we will fail. What happens when we get to the good soil?

We don't know what is the good soil until we sow the seed.

Studying the life of Praying Hyde (died with callous on his knees.) Everywhere where praying Hyde was praying those villages were receptive. Many times we are not going to know if a group is responsible or not if we are sowing in a good soil. Don't be discouraged. That is why He says to sow everywhere. He might later ripen or make the soil better in another harvest but no guarantees.

We sow everywhere to find good soil to invest in. Keep a vision for the fruit.

